\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14361825 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Aigburth House, Aigburth Vale, Liverpool 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And your marital status? You're a widower, aren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your year of marriage, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 1922, I think near enough. I haven't got me marriage lines now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your year of birth, please.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 1898.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 To}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942532\charrsid10310113 x}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
worth Park, Carleton Hill, Liverpool 8. It is 8 now, it wasn't then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How many years did you live in the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the house I was born? Oh, I couldn't say. Probably 2 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And where did you live then, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In Fernhill Street, still in Toxworth Park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And how many years did you live in Fernhill Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 A couple of years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you think where you went from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, we got a house of our own in Cam Street, Liverpool 8.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How long were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I was there until I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 . I'd be there from ... I'd say from ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would it be up to 1918, or past then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It'd be up to 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember why the family made these moves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. I believe that 
I was born in the house where my father and mother were in apartments and so they moved to better apartments, better accommodation when we moved into apartments in Fernhill Street. And then we eventually got a house in Cam Street and then we moved for ...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And the house in Cam Street was the one you stayed in for all that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And that was your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That was my home, yes. Oh, wait a minute. Wait a minute, now. Don't let me run away here. We lived in Handel Street, that's Live
rpool 8, off Lodge Lane, and we lived there for quite a few years, and that was a 4 roomed house, and through the same landlord - that was Smith }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3736850 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  Sons - Mother, being a good rent-payer, I suppose, and good character and that, we got this house in Cam Street. So that'd be between leaving Fernhill Street, going to Handel Street, and from Handel Street to Cam Street.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, which of those houses did you live the most in? Did you live most of your childhood in Cam Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think most of my childhood up to 1918, as you say, well, must be in Cam Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 There was 8 in the family. I had one brother killed in the first World War, and meself, and then I had 3 other brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Let's go through their ages and spacing. Are you the youngest, or the eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I'm the eldest living now. The eldest one got killed in action. Then I come second, and then there's 3 other brothers after me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, how many years' difference between you and the next brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Albert? Oh, about 3 years, roughly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And then the next one after that? How many years' difference between Albert and the next brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Between 2 and 3 years. They were all quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In sort of batches of 3 years? And another brother, did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Three brothers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's including the one who was killed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The one killed in action, no he was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And this was roughly 3 years again, was it, after that? Did you have any sisters? You said there were 8 of you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. I have 2 sisters dead, one living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did the sisters come in the family? Were they younger or older than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 One was the eldest of the family, but she died, like, when she was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How many years older was she than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She'd 
be about ... I should say about 5 or 6 years at least. Because then there was the brother that I told you got killed. Well then, he was second in command and I come third.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, where did the other sisters come? How many years below you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, there was a bit between. One sister was the eldest; one sister was two below me, and the other sister was about 4 below me, I think.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So did they come ... the girls and boys didn't all come in a series of 3 years? Was there less difference between the girl
s than there were with the boys?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes difference in years before their birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, I think there was ... well spaced out between them, you know. The eldest one would be about ... she'd have been about 77 now, I should think. So she'd be 5 years 
older than me now. The one next to me, that died recently well, she was round about the 60, just over 60. The one now ... the one that is living now, she'd be round 58, 60.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I couldn't say that. I don't know what age he was when he got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, do you remember what age he was when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, he was getting well on, he was over ... when he died, he died about 1945. '46, and I'd be ... I'm trying to work off meself, you see. 1946 - 1898, that's 48. He was about 80, 80-odd, I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Eighty-odd when he died. Now how old would you say he was when you were born? You'd say about 44-ish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When I was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, no. We'll have to cut that down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How old was your father when you were born, Mr. Mainey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 About 30 to 33.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Liverpool.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What was his occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, his main occupation, when I was growing older, it was ... was that he was a freight clerk on a line o
f docks. Dock labourer, if you understand, but employed as a freight clerk. But in his younger days he was a clerk to the Belgian Consul, Mr. \{ILLEGIBLE\}?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was that his first job, as clerk to the Belgian Consul?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think he got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
 from that, I'm not sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And then he went to the docks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Then he went to the docks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And did he have any jobs after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, not 'till he retired. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So he just had the 2 jobs as far as you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Two jobs, yes. Only worked for the Dock Board and did the crane driving for the Dock Board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But it was all in the docks?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mostly docks, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, did he also do any casual or part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember your father ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We
ll, yes, because ... through no fault of his own, but as the dock rules in Liverpool, or the Dock Statements are, that ... they used to call it '3 on the hook and 3 on the book'. That meant you worked with a hook in your belt ... that was a docker's weapo
n
, you know, the docker's hook, and the 3 on the book was where you had to stand 3 days on the dole, you see. 'Course, if there was a big rush of traffic, or plenty of ships about, well then they got plenty of work all the time. But then periodically then 
it used to come about that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How often would this happen, that he'd be out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, in his latter years it was a few years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Quite a few occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, how old was your mother when you were born? Was she younger or older than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mother? I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you think she was roughly the same age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I should think about the same age, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 About 30 to 33?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did your mother come from, was she a Liverpool girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She was from Liverpool, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she have any jobs before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, she was a housewife all her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But she never worked before she }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And he didn't work at all after she was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And no part time jobs, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I'd like to ask you now about life at home when you were a child, the time up to when you left school. How many rooms were there in the house at Cam Street? This was the one you lived the longest in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That was a six-roomed house, the one in Cam Street. Three up and 3 down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 There were 3 bedrooms upstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Three bedrooms, and then there was parlour, kitchen and back kitchen downstairs, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brothers and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No relatives or friends or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. We might have put a cousin or an uncle or someone like that up for a couple of nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But this was only a visitor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Temporary, yes. No regular visitors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was the washing done at home, or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 At home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. Oh, Mother. Mother mi
ght have made ... oh, yes, she might have made little things for us, you know. Not suits, not suits of clothes, but vests, or a little pullover, you might have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Any dress-making? Anything for the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, she used to do a bit for the girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And of course, mending, I presume?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes! Always plenty of socks to darn (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were the clothes that you had new or secondhand when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, or clothes were more often new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you occasionally have secondhand ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where would your mother have bought the clothes? Was there a particular shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 On the cheque.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And where would she go? Would there be a particular shop?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The Provident Clothing Hall, as I can remember that as a child, and I'd got a nice suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sort of place is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It's a gentlemen's outfitters, you know, like ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 A big store?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 A tailor's. Right opposite Kelly's in Renshaw Street, it's still there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about the girls, where would their clothes have been bought? What kind of store would she have gone to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, most likely Sturbers, I should think, if they were going in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's a big departmental store, really, rather than a small shop, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. Oh, The
 Grand Clothing Hall, was the name of it. The Grand Clothing Hall was the name of the gentlemen's outfitters. Just by Central Hall there, that's where it it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When did you have new clothes. When did you and your brothers and sisters have new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, whenever me mother thought we could do with a new set.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You had to wait until they were worn out, you mean, before you ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, not work out, she was pretty keen on us ... how we looked, and that
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She liked you to look nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She was very proud.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about shoes? Were your shoes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mostly new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your father didn't make shoes for you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where would the shoes have been bought, what kind of shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Same kind of shop, from the
 cheque shop. Everyone gave you cheques, you could work anything out because there was such a lot. I can remember there was L.C., Park, Provident and all the lot, but to people the departmental stores ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When would you have had new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, always for special occasions, and we would make sure of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you keep a pair for best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And a pair for every day, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you'd keep a pair for best, then when you got a new pair, they'd be for everyday, would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes, and for special occasions, like, if we were going to a party or something like that and we had to keep up with the others although we were perhaps the poorest of the lot. But we had to keep tabs. Case of keeping up with the Joneses (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house? Such as the cleaning, or the cooking, or washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, Mother was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942532\charrsid10310113 house-proud}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 , but I think he did help her, especially if she was not too well, or anything like that. She didn't suffer, like, to any great extent, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 There were times when she'd to ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 As the family came along, anyway. Yes, he used to help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there any particular jobs that he did? Clear out the fires, or any decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
He'd clear the fire out, or if he could do a little bit of washing or anything like that, you know. Of course, the girls ... the girls, as they grew up naturally, they'd come into it. Yes, I think he did show his hand, a bit, like. He wasn't idle, anyway.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, what about decorating or repairs, or improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, she was very proud, my mother was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your father, did he do any of these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I don't think she'd let him (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She'd do them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, she'd do them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would she decorate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's what I mean, oh, everything. Oh, aye, even get up and whitewash the ceiling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father ever dress you or undress you or bath you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, we used to have a bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When would he have done this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When we were school children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And he would take his turn, would he, to do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, there would have to be an occasion, like, that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mother couldn't do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, he didn't do a lot of reading to us, but he used to tell us stories of all sorts, such as interesting ones about the world, travel, or it might be comical stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But you remember him telling you quite a lot of stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, he was an expert at that. He had a good sense of humour, same as I've got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And this came through in his stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, he might put a bit of his own version to it, you know, but always above level, you know, there was nothing out of place, lik
e. But he used to love telling us stories about when he was doing a little bit of a turn somewhere, you know, he was in a concert party, so was I, like, years ago, but something that happened there, you know, tickled him funny, or funny comedians, that so
rt of thing. He'd tell you some of the wisecracks, you know, that brought the laughs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So you'd look forward to that, would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. Oh, yes. Say it was a wet evening and we weren't feeling like going out, well 'come on, let's go and get me D
ad to tell us a couple of stories', you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And did he look after you when she was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. Oh, I don't say he looked after us when she was out. Oh, no, I think when we we
re getting up we pretty well looked after ourselves, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you were smaller, though, would she have gone out and left him to look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home? To he
lp your father and mother? Did you have any particular jobs that you had to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, I don't think I did have any particular jobs to do. I always made it me business to keep meself regularly employed so's I could help them financially, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, but this is going back in your childhood, you know. Did you ever have any jobs at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we used to do ... oh, not anything special, like, you know. Odd jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about your brothers and sisters, did they have any regular jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We
ll, they used to make it their business, like, to be the little mothers, if you understand. You know, like, they wouldn't see Mother lug a bowl full of dishes or a wash basin full of dishes, or anything like that without they wouldn't be in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They would help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, definitely.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the older children help the younger children with things they found difficult, such as dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. My brother, the one that got killed, he used to help me if anything was out of place; if 
me tie was crooked or ... we used to have bows in them days and they were supposed to be one side up and one side down. Oh, yes, they were pretty keen all round on how we went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they look after the smaller ones in any way, did they take care of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
They took us out and that, you know, and of course, we passed it on to ours when we got on, same. I used to walk mine one time every Sunday morning from Lodge Lane right through this park to the Vale here and get a car to Garston and then walk
 to ... oh, right round Oglett Road, round that way, and to the farm houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the younger children help the older ones in any way when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, not unless it was something to do with their homework and they knew something about it 
and we didn't (laughter). No, I think we all worked on the same system, we all helped each other, like, 'cos we got on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your school days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What time would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, roughly about ... well, taking the year all round, 8 o'clock. No later.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother, or anyone else, put you to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was it your mother, or was it somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, Mother used to do that. Like, when we were real infants. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you remember at what age you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. I was about 10 or 11 when I used to put meself to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you share the bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, in them days, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me how you slept when you were small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We had two in a bed, and I think at the outside we had 3.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It was a double bed in your bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Double bed, yes. And that was 2 sleeping one end and one sleeping at the other. That was in the four rooms. Of course, when we got t
o 6 rooms we were very posh, we had room to move, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would your parents have a bedroom to themselves, or would they have children in with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I have a slight idea ... wait a minute, I think in those days ... I think Father and Mot
her had all of us in their bedroom at some time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have other beds in their bedroom, or did you sleep in the same bed as your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Slept in the same bed. It's only ... I don't think it would be above 2 or 3 of us. I don't know about meself, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was when you had 3 bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, this was in the 4-roomed. No, Cam Street we were well off, we had 3 bedrooms, well, they had the one room to themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So they would have their own bedroom, and then 4 children in each bedroom, if there were 8 of you at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, there was meself and 3 brothers in one room, and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Me sisters, I think the 3 of them had ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you have had single beds in the sisters' room, or one big double bed and
 they all slept in that? Or would you have had 2 single beds, or 3 single beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Most probably .... Well, I think we had 2 beds in each room, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What room did you bath in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We didn't have a bath in any room. We didn't have a ... only w
hen we were getting after leaving school, like. We'd take a bath of water upstairs and ... But otherwise it'd be mostly downstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Whereabouts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, in the wintertime, in front of the fire, with a big sheet over you, something like that, you s
ee. Maybe, if we had enough towels for everybody we took it in different turns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have a big tin bath in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Big enamel bowl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you had a wash down, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, a real good one, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How often did you have this wash down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Regularly. Regularly. Every week. Sometimes twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Depending if you'd fallen in the mud, or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's right. That's ... referring to the original cleanliness ... bath, same as I have mine here every Wednesday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Every week, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did this coincide with your wash down in front of the fire?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You'd have them after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Used to get the nightie put on and perhaps a little ves
t, or something like that, you see and your clean socks and that would be up in the room, you'd put them on Saturday morning. Very keen on cleanliness, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did the family have their meals, mostly, in Cam Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there any occasions when they ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Unless it'd be a party, something like that, a kiddies' party, but if it's the general family ... I should think if Mother wasn't well, or something like that on occasions we might have had som
e in the parlour. Mostly kitchen, say kitchen definitely. That's where I ate nearly all mine, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did your mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She cooked in the home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The kitchen that you ate in, or the back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She used to ... Well, first of all we had the gas cooker, like, and then of course, we had the fireplace with the oven alongside it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You had the range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. You know, the old fireplaces, where we used to put the potatoes in their jackets, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about the ovens, and things? She had a range, she used to cook in the oven, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And later on she had a gas stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, as time went on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you had this gas stove, did you have this gas stove in the kitchen where you ate or did you have it in the back kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But of course the range would have been in the kitchen where you ate, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When was breakfast eaten? About what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, you could say around about 8 o'clock of a morning, on account of us getting off to school, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What members of the family were present for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, it'd be all those that were of school age.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about your mother and father, would they have breakfast with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, Mother might have hers with me father, because if he was going down to the docks for 8 o'clock, or half past seven, well, he'd have to have breakfast by half past 6. The working man's breakfast, you know. It might only be a piece of toast, or somethin
g like that, but something to keep him going, like, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And your mother would have had it with him, would she, and then she'd have given breakfast to all you children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, she'd have had something with him, like. A cup of tea and perhaps 
a piece of toast. Then perhaps she might have had a bit of breakfast later on. 'Course, we'd be gone to school, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She'd sit in peace and quiet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's just it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you usually eat and drink? Now you say there was a spot of toast, did you have anything else for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, we may have a little bit of bacon but there wasn't a great lot, like, in them days to go round. I'd say we lived mostly on a bit of porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You had porridge, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Winter and summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, winter and summer, yes. We'd have a bit of porridge and more often than not a piece of toast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about Sundays, would that be any different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we'd have a Sunday breakfast, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It might be boiled egg and toast; it might be a little bit of bacon and egg, or it might be a poached egg, or fried, egg, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It would be something cooked, though, for a change?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of things would you have had for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, well, we'd have all sorts. Mother might make a hotpot, during the morning she might make a big meat pie and then we'd come home and have that. And if she'd anything special on, such as washing day well, of course, you'd have to put up with whatev
er you got. It might be fish and chips, you see, chips, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But she did meat pie and hotpot. Anything else you can remember having?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, Sundays, we had a good dinner Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about Sundays?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, such as roast beef and a bit of Yorkshire pudding, if the wages ran it. Rabbit, roast rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of puddings would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We had all the milky puddings. We have had, like, what you call steamed puddings, but I think it was mostly rice and tapioca.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She used to cook it in the oven for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mother did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, every week. I know, I've had tired arms, you know, giving a hand to knead the bread, and we did knead it!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she make her own jam, or bottle fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She used to mostly buy jam. She has made jam, I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about bottling fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think she bottled anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she make any pickles or wine, or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If she made medicines it would be something to keep the bowels ... in order, I'll tell you that, as well be ... about that, er, ...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she make up her own medicines, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think so. She used to give us such things as Gregory powders and liquorice powders, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father ever have a go at making beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not your mother, either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. Not to my knowledge, anyway. Mother was strong teetotal. Father liked his pints.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But she never got around to tasting it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. She might have a little glass of Port wine at Christmas, or something like that, you know, but she wasn't a drinker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, we had no ground for it, you see. It was all bought.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they buy any tinned, or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Any dried fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, it's a long time to think out, isn't it. I was wondering if she ever bought any of these dehydrated potatoes, anything like that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I don't think they had them then, would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I doubt it. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they keep any livestock for the family, such as hens, pigs or goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. We had a rabbit one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But you didn't have it to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, no. (laughter), not for the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How many times a week do you think you had meat? Or tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Meat? We had ... on Friday, we always ha
d fish Friday, I can tell you that. I'd say almost every day, one way or the other. Even if it was only a little bit of stew or scouse, that's the Liverpool ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 A little made to go a long way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you have for your tea during the week? Your evening meal, what kind of thing would you have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Might have had a bit of cheese and lettuce, or might have a bit of something warm if it was required. And we might have a homemade pasty, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever get some extra meat, such as rabbit, from poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember seeing your mother have less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You do remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father have more to eat than the rest of you and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think they were all ... I think they were both pretty co-operative in that way, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You mean if the food was short they would let you children ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They made sure that we had ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And they'd go short themselves, you mean, so that you children would have enough?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, they'd get less than what we were having.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you allowed to talk during meals, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, they were very ... we have spoken during meals, but the rule in our hous
e was that you go to the table to eat, and keep your talking until eating's over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you keep to that fairly regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We did pretty well, yes. And another ruling was that nobody'd move from the table until everybody had finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked, or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, no. Oh, no. If you ... hear somebody say 'Mother, I don't think I could eat that', 'cos we may have had a couple of cakes outside, or something like that, you see. Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would your mother say if you said 'I don't want that'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She'd say 'well, do you feel all right', like, 'you're not off colour'. Say, 'I just don't feel like it'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What was your parents' attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They used to tell us off about it. 'Why don't you clean the plate?' That was their attitude. They liked to see clean plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass
 it to you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, we used to have to say 'pass it over, please'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, if we felt like it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way, and sit in a certain way at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, we were supposed to sit properly at the table, as Mother used to say, 'let your food digest and let it go down to your stomach', and she said, 'don't be sitting with your legs cross
ed or your arms round your back', or something like that, you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about your knife and fork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, we were taught very early how to use those. 'Course, what we didn't have in those days, I'll tell you, was fish knives, 
you know, like we have now. If they'd given us one of those, well, we'd have had to ask what was that for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You wouldn't have known what it was for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I wouldn't, not in our day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, i
f you did you wouldn't put it on the table, you'd put your book on your knees, you know, until you'd finished your meal. But that didn't happen very often, as they insisted that the table was for your food. That's the dining table, but I wouldn't say that
 we haven't taken them and I wouldn't say that we have taken them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But this was the general rule?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The general rule was manners at the table, and how to use the tools that were given to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal? Every meal that you had? Well, obviously your father would be out at lunchtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, and then he may be out at night, you know, or he may be working overtime. Those that were available, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If your father was in he would sit with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 He would sit with us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, not always. More often than not, but ... see, it just depends on the room, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But there wasn't a regular place for you and you wouldn't ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, y
ou had your regular place, but you didn't always sit in that place, you understand what I mean. There may be 2 or 3 out, they may have gone to play football in the park, or gone somewhere else, well then you'd make the best use of the table. No, normally,
 like, it was pretty well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You had your own favourite spot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How was the meal served? Was it served by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she serve from the saucepans straight onto the places, or did she put the food in a ser
ving dish and put that on the table and then serve it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She more often than not served it right from the saucepan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What order were you served it? Were the children served first, or Father served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I couldn't say anything about the system in that, but I think it was just a matter of how she thought fit, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you remember whether your father was served first, or last?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think it was the general rule that if Father was at home, like, ... I don't think it really ru
ns into anybody being served first. The meals were put down and we used to more often than not wait until all the meals were down and then we'd say our little prayer before meals ... Grace before meals, as you say. Well, Father used to say that, and we'd 
all dig in. There was no priority, I don't think, as far as somebody being served first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did the younger brothers and sisters sit before they could feed themselves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, they'd have been given their meals ... probably if it was cold, 
near enough to the fire. You know, they'd perhaps sit on the big carpet in front of the fire, and if there were little chairs for them, well then they'd sit on those, or else a stool. Mother used to make a lot of these here rugs, if you'd like to call the
m, out of old clothes, and that, you know. Well, we used to help her to make them, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They were nice and cosy and warm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, lovely. Lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And they wear well, too, don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother feed the little ones when they were small and couldn't feed themselves, or did the older brothers and sisters do this?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We used to do our share, like, we'd do our share in feeding them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Everyone would muck in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, what we used to call in them days, the pubs (?)
 or whatever they were getting, bread and milk, anything like that. Oh, yes, we'd ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
When were they able to join in family meals? Were they sort of put in a high chair to the table or did they wait until they were big enough to sit in an ordinary chair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no, if there was room at the table they were put on a chair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How would they be fixed on a chair if they were very tiny? Would they sit on cushions, or ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, they'd have the tallest chair, I think. I don't think we were all that well off for cushions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was your mother and easy person to talk to when you were very tiny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, yes, very friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If you had any worries could you share them with her, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, yes. She always liked you to be open and if anything was troubling you, let her know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you would always feel you could, no matter what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, if there was anything you wanted to hide, well then, of course, that would be your prerogative, bu
t if you had anything that was really genuine and straight up, well then yes. She had every feeling for you and she'd go to no ... end of the world to ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 To do what she could for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about your father, was he an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I must tell the truth that he was very easy and a very clever man, until he'd had one over the eight, and then he was very awkward.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did he get more difficult when he'd had a spot to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In what way would he be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, you couldn't approach him like you could if he was sober, you see. And then, another thing is that probably he wouldn't feel up to answering questions, or anything like that, you know. You couldn't go to him and say, 'Dad, would you li
ke to help me with me homework, tonight?' If you see he'd had one or two you'd try and work the happy medium.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When he hadn't had a spot to drink, was he then an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, very interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And did he show you any affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, he didn't show, like, great affection, but he would assist you in anything you wanted to do, like. I mean to say, such as your homework, or anything you wanted to know about what comes from India, and what comes from these places, like, for 
your own education. I was always asking questions. As far as helping you financially, well, it wasn't just the case.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I didn't really mean that, you know, it was something that ... What I'm trying to get at is what you felt about him. Did he show his a
ffection in any way, or if you had any worries would you have gone to him and talked about them with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, if he was sober. I wouldn't go to him in any ... in any liquor, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But normally you could?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Because you might
 just come one day and you'd have a row with him and then, of course, the dirty washing might come out. We used to just leave well alone so far as that was ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They expected us to respect them. And we did do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Anything else that you'd like to add?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, we used to respect them in the way they brought us up, the way they taught us our manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your brothers and sisters in certain ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, we all had to sort of love each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You don't remember your parents suggesting how you behaved towards your brothers and sisters, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, you had to behave, like, in a proper gentlemanly way to them. Oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, did they say you should hit back, or not, if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
They never told us to hit back, they told us to come and tell them. If they did it, and then they used to go up and see their parents, and try to find out why, you see. If I went in
 with a cut face, or a cut ear, or something like that, they'd want to know why I'd got it, what I'd done to deserve it. Oh, yes, Mother used to go up and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She'd sort it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Sort it out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, they hoped that things would get better than what they were in the living line, and that we could progress ourselves to be better off than what they were financially, and ... in every way possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Quite a lot of things they thought were important. I mean to say, the first one was to make yourself liked by everybody; keep yourself clean and neat and tidy and be able to speak to peop
le as ... sort of ... a gentleman would do. In other words, in general to show respect to everybody and to be able to approach them and feel that you're ... you know, like, you're getting yourself up in the world. They never had any thoughts of keeping yo
u down, they always wanted you to get on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, we never were allowed to swear in their presence, although we did swear (laughter). Well, if I was playing football and got a kick somewhere where I didn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about themselves, did they ever swear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, Mother never hardly swore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I could say this ... I'd rather say that me father could speak six languages, and seven when he was drunk (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But they didn't approve of you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 swearing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  and you didn't ever swear in front of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When grownups were talking, were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, Mother said it wasn't manners to join in. Wait until you're asked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If you did something that your parents disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, we got the works, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What do you mean by 'the works'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, me father, if he'd been told and he found out it was true, well, we used to get the strap.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your father would always punish you, or your mother would sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, Mother would hardly ever punish us. She' might just box your ears, or something like that, but not anything severe. But me father would tell you 'get upstairs'. I've had it, not so very often, once or 
twice ... something I did, I think I stole an apple, or something ... and you used to have to get hold of the bedrail and the strap'd come out and that'd be 2 or 3 on your back and you wouldn't be eager to do it again in a hurry. He didn't like doing it b
ut oh, he felt it his job to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Apart from the apple that you stole and got punished for it, can you remember any particular occasion when you were punished - apart from that? Can you think of any other reasons why you were given the strap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I can't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember how you felt about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You felt very sore about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you feel towards your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I used to feel towards me father that there must have been a reason for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You felt that he was justified?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That he was justified in doing it, that he'd found out the truth, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you deserved what you got, is this what you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to
 behave from both your parents, or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, they both taught us, but Mother was keen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, would you say that one or the other had more influence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I'd say that they both were responsible for our good manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you receive any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, we received presents and if the money would run it we'd have a little party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you'd have some friends to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you have anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, we might have a bit extra, yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9925485\charrsid10310113 because}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9925485\charrsid10310113 it was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  for that day. '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9925485\charrsid10310113 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 ourse, 2 or 3 of the neighbours'd probably give us a few coppers, you know, say 'it's your birthday on S
aturday, here', and of course, the coppers we'd give to Mother and Mother would put it towards perhaps some chocolate biscuits or a nice fancy cake.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever have a birthday cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, have a birthday cake, and a bit of blancmange and jelly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you remember anything you did with your mother and father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, naturally enough, first thing we'd have to do is ... well, you'd have a look at your stocking first of all, well, I used to do ... I used to say to meself, 'well ....'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, we were talking about Christmas and what you had in your stocking, and you were saying you had a little toy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We'd have an apple, an orange, one cracker, a piece of coal (laughter), small piece of coal for luck. You m
ay have a chip - I don't mean a chip potato - a chip with the coal, to light the coal. And you may inside your stocking get a small stocking, you know, one of these that you get from a sweet shop, or something like that. There might be a few dolly mixture
s and a little puzzle or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now what kind of thing did you do on Christmas Day? What kind of lunch, for instance? What was Christmas Dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we had according to what was ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 According to how much money was available?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you have always had a chicken, or would you sometimes not been able to have afforded one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes. Oh, no, we were always provided with a Christmas Dinner, you know, usually it was only a chicken, or a bit of beef or whatever it was.
 A bit of pork. And the trimmings, like, stuffing, etc. But of course, those days ... those days things were much cheaper and probably managed a table off it, you see. Mother used to join these Christmas Clubs, such as the butcher. Say, she might go in an
d
 this weekends meat would be 4/3d. or 4/6d. and she'd put five bob down and put the ninepence or sixpence towards the Christmas. And then when she had the Christmas and found out what she wanted, well the butcher'd soon tell her how much she'd got in and 
how much she'd have to find. Of course, we were always pretty helpful in trying to help out on anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This of course was when you were older, when you were earning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. We went out shopping and of course, I used to get one or 2 
little Christmas boxes from customers that I delivered to, you see, and it all made ... Well, some of it went in, some went towards shoes or stockings or anything her wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you do on Christmas afternoon or Christmas morning, for instance, as a family? How did you spend the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, we used to get round the fire and tell some little stories we'd been told at school, what happened here or what happened there. And then there was always the pantomime, you know, at the Pavilion Theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was on Christmas afternoon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, to the matinee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was this a regular thing, or would you only go some Christmas days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, if there was one we didn't like we wouldn't go .. Some Christmas days, yes. Well, the other one, we'd go out
 and go to the ... if it was fit to go out, we'd go down to the park and see some of these junior football teams, or things like that, to pass the afternoon, like. And then back home for tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the evening, of course, it 
would be the usual ... go down and sing carols. Even before Christmas we might some of them go down singing carols, get another couple of coppers that way. More for the kitty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who would play that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
We'd have to try and get somebody in. Well, I had a chap when I was in a concert party, he used to come and bang a note or two out for us, you know. No, we never had nobody ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not actually in the home who played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 My sister did start going to music and then she packed it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You liked singing, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And did you have a singsong in the house, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no. We just had a little tune amongst ourselves, like, but not like a party or a do, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You didn't make music together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes. Oh, aye. All this hide and seek business and Find The Thimble, and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there any books in the house when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of books would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Such as The Swiss Family Robinson, or ... interesting story books, I'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about newspapers or magazines, did your parents have newspapers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we had the newspaper, the evening paper and the Sunday paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not a morning paper, though, just the evening paper and Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't recollect ever having the morning paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about magazines? Any magazines you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I think there was one or 2.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mother used to do when she was ... And Father, yes, they both used to read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they ever read aloud to you or two each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If there was anything we wanted to know and they had a book with it, well they'd always read it to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember a funeral in the family when you were a young child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Let me see ... yes. When I was a young child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, up to 1918, then, but this really is up to your schooldays. During your schooldays, can you remember a funeral?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, me elder sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who attended that funeral? How old was she when she died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I should think she'd be about ... couldn't really say her age. Say about 15.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who attended the funeral? Who would have come to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I should think some of the family relations. I can't remember the funeral. There was a funeral, like, in the family, but
 I can't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you remember what kind of clothes people wore, mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Mostly black, was mostly the ... it seemed to be the regulation, I think, with the majority of people. If they couldn't have black, well then they showed 
respect by putting a bit of black on the ... their arm, the sleeve. But the majority could afford it, like, they used to wear black clothes. If they couldn't wear a black suit they'd probably have a dark overcoat, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When your sister ... her funeral, can you tell me who went to the funeral from your family? Did you all go, all her brothers and sisters?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, I think she ... wait a minute, though, I'm trying to think back a bit now. I think I was recalled from the Army to co
me back home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This would be when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This would be my other sister, about 19-- ... oh, I'd be 18 years of age, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And of course, the family was split up a bit then, if they were older?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I just forget, now. To be honest, I just forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you taken out visiting neighbours, friends or relations when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 With whom? Who would have taken you out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, Father might take us out, or Mother and Father might come with us. You see, say 
'well, there's a party on at Auntie Gin's, or Auntie Mag's, or Auntie Flo's and you've been invited to go up there, ' you see. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you taken shopping at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 By whom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Mother, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, we did, Saturday night, to the theatre.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was this a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 More often than not, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What was the theatre? A music hall or variety?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The Liverpool Olympia, or the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8942532\charrsid10310113 Hippodrome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 . Variety, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember any other outings with your parents? You've mentioned that sometimes you went out on the Christmas afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we've been to other outings. Been to New Brighton. Go to Seacombe and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8942532\charrsid10310113 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 alk to New Brighton on the sands and all that sort. Oh, yes, we done all that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Anything else you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Whenever they could get us out, like, they did. Mostly me mother, though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about Bank Holidays, what sort of thing would you have done on a Bank Holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We used to save up our coppers for Bank Holiday and we used to take sandwiches with us and that, and perhaps go to Thurstaston or Upton.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 These are local beauty spots, country beauty spots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. We'd mostly make for New Brighton and work out from there. Sometimes
 we'd make for Woodside Station and go up Thurstaston, round that way. 'Course the object was when we got there was to have a football match, or a game of football. And then we used to have a little primus stove and make the tea and have the sandwiches, t
he come home dead beat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Dirty, but happy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever go away for a holiday in your school days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I did, being a clever boy at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I went to Ramsey in the Isle of Man. From Liverpool Education Committee through Mr. R.D. Holt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The shipping man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes. I don't know how it came about, I can't give you the foundation of the story, like, but the clever children in certain schools and certain classes were picked out for this and I was one. 
And we went to Ramsey, under canvas and we used to have an Army }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 sergeant}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
 major and I don't know whether the men with him, they would be Army men in civvies, and we were put in this field ... boys, like, we were and we went up Snaefell Mountain and all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You enjoyed it, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, every bit of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was this the only holiday you had as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I think it was. That's as a schoolchild, like. Oh, no, wait a minute, I've got one more. I worked for a fishmonger in Agnes Road,
 here, named Tipping, used to be right in the dip of Agnes Road and Alwyn Street, and his father and mother had a cottage outside Shrewsbury, and me brother and I worked there so this was before the First World War. And they sent us away for a fortnight a
n
d the object in the back of their mind was they were going to give us a holiday and feed us well, which they did, looked after us the best way they could and we made ourselves very handy by getting the damsons and the pears and the nuts for the shells, wi
th the leaf on the outside. And then we helped in a farm }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 next door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
 and ... old Brown's Farm when they were cutting the hay down, for the rabbits. That's one I shall always remember because there was a rabbit catcher with us, you know, and this chap used to 
lay on the ground and I would stand beside Mrs. Brown and he got one rabbit, you know, and he threw it. I don't think Mrs. Brown was very ... you know, she was looking the other way. I'll tell you this, now. It's really funny. And the rabbit hit her in th
e
 stomach, you know and she conked out (laughter). I think she thought something had flew at her, you know, I don't think she was prepared for it. She must have forgotten that this chap was there. We were on the boundary line, you know, save 'em running aw
ay. We had sticks to beat them down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days? Remember, this is before you worked, while you were still at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 By going to the park and watching football, or going and playing football, or crick
et, or whatever ... you know, was going on. Unless Mother wanted us to go any messages, like, we always made sure that we did those, and then after that, well, that's it. If she said 'right', off we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How about Sundays, how would you have spent Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Always go to Church, for a start off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What time of the day would you have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 About 9 o'clock, 10 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. And Sunday School in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You went twice a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 More often than not, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have different clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, always had our best suit, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you play games, or did your parents think it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, no. We played games on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents attend a place of worship, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, me father did in his younger days, but of course, he got out of the fashion and me mother, no, she never went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When your father was younger and he did attend church, what denomination would it have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 R.C.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And your Church was R.C., too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there any Sunday School outings? Can you remember any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I can't remember any, not from our Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What other social activities organised by the Church that you went to did you take part in? Can you think of any activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I was a sports secretary, and I was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Remember, this is in your schooldays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, in my schooldays, no. Any other activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, I was always keen on singing the songs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you used to sing in the choir, did you, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I used to sing in the choir, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any outings for the choir, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not that I can recall, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the Church that you belonged to run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were either of your parents a member of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you belong to any other club organised by the Church? At that time when you were of school age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, the only thing that I belonged to during me school age until I was about 11 or 12 was the Boy Cadets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where would that have been run from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 From Vine Street, off }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 Myrtle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This wasn't anything to do with the Church, this was Separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no, thi
s was separate. Same as the Boy Scouts or the Boys' Brigade, 'course, they were mostly run from churches, I know, but this was just ... you dressed up like a soldier and that was it. You wanted to be able to go round showing all the girls how nice you loo
ked in uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 With little flat hats, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was Grace said at meals in your family? Now, I think you mentioned this before. Was it always said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, more often than not. We may have missed on occasions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, me father if he was there, and then we used to say it after him, like. We all took part in it, to be honest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever have family prayers? Apart from the Grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, we never all got down together, oh, no. But you'd say your prayers before you went to bed, or first thing in the morning, like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not active.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 His views were Liberal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Why do you think he held these liberal views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I suppose it was the policy that suited him, that's the only reason I can say why.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about your mother, did she take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she have any views, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no, she didn't have any views, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Do you remember your parents talking about any issues, or if they had any views about who should govern the country, or if they thought the working man had a square deal? Can you remember them ever talking like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, they used to ... I've heard me father talk about his opinion of why he thought they should run the country, you see, and of course, one of his party slogans in those days was "Free Trade and Tariff Reform"
. That was the Liberal policy. I remember that, anyway, quite well, but ... what was the question you asked me, again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I just wondered whether you'd heard them talking about any issues that ... or did they have any particular views about who should go
vern the country, but obviously your father liked the Liberals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, yes, he was ... he voted Liberal, I know that, you see, but I don't think that they'd seem to have the opinion then as what they have now, I think, and the general opinion now is, na
turally enough, that they're all there for their own ends. You see, they get voted and they're there, but the point is that you've got to rather get interested in one or the other. I do, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And sort of try and weigh one up against the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
The average, I'm not speaking only for meself, now, I'm speaking like for the average person in the country, the majority, you talk to them on this, that or the other, they say 'well when they get there what do they do? They're all there for their own en
ds'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember your father or your mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 General election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You remember them both voting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You mentioned to me that your father was Liberal. Did both your parents vote Liberal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I couldn't say what Mother voted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, I say he voted Liberal because he was Liberal at heart, you know, his political views, like. My opinion is that he voted Liberal. As regards me mother, well ... that's only my opinion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if your father felt under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, I don't think so because, as I say, Father's work was only casual, so even if he voted for somebody, it was a casual affair, he'd still have his time to play out, wouldn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You said your father had views. You did say he wasn't a member of a political party, didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 He wasn't. Do you remember him working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, seeing as he's a casual dock labourer, well ... I think, I may be mistaken, but I think Bowerings were Liberals, t
he ship owners and of course, if he was on a line of docks he's bound to be employed sometime or other working for that firm, wouldn't he.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And he would have been helping indirectly, you mean, with the general election? By working for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 For the firm? Oh, no, he'd be directed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 He'd be directed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
He'd be directed to the job through this here Port Authorities. Well, those days they used to have what was call The Stand, at the docks, where the men used to have to muster and make a 
stand outside the shed where they thought there'd be a job, and somebody would get picked on for the job and then the others would ... 'well, that's all today', walk round. If it was a freight clerk they were short of, and me father was a freight clerk an
d they knew, well, all right, he went as a freight clerk there, 'tell Fred Mainey to come and join so-and-so gang', you see. Only checking cargo, like. They call them freight clerks, but ... freight, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I don't know whether I ever found me mother when she hadn't got something to do. She'd always find something to do, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would she ever go out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, she'd go out, like, perhaps for an hou
r or so she'd go and see Auntie Kate or Auntie Gin and have a little talk. You females know more when it comes to family business. She might be in a dilemma about something, so 'I'll go and ask her opinion', and that's it, you see. It might be making clot
hes, it might be anything. That's it, she went out, but she didn't make a habit of going out a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about your father, what would he have done? He liked his pint in the evening, probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, when he had the money. And his pipe, and he'
d got a paper and a book and sit by the fire with his slippers on, and that would be it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Then he'd be more keen to stay in than go out, really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, it would be a case that his picket was empty, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This really organised things for him, whether he had anything to spend on anything to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Did your mother, apart from going out to see relatives, did she have any interests at all outside the home? For instance, did she belong to any clubs, or ladies' clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself? Would she ever have gone out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, not to any great extent. I think she was 100% family, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When did your father get home from work in the evenings? Now, I think you mentioned }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 earlier}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  to me that sometimes he was on shift work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, overtime. Well, the average day at the docks used to be, stop at 5 or half past, so you could say the majority of days he'd be home about 6 o'clock you see. But if it come to overtime, well he might work 'till 7 or 9 at night, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Just depended if it came up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Just depended what the ship was, the cargo, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How many evenings a week would he spend at home? You mentioned that if he had money in his pocket he would like to go for h
is pint, so how many evenings a week do you think he would have spent at home? On an average?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
On an average? Oh, well, taking the good and the bad I should think he'd spend about 5 nights a week at home. The weekend'd be mostly his ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 His night
 for going out, yes. Did your father attend any clubs? Or pubs? Now, I know he liked his drink, so he often attended a pub. What about clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't know of any clubs, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother ever go with him at all to anywhere in the evenings? Did they ever go out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, might've been out a few times, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your mother ever go to a pub with him for a drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no. She didn't drink.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, he was very interested in football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did he either play it or watch it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, he used to watch it. But I think he was ... I think, now, I'm not too sure ... amateur football was his line that I ... I think that he was a committee man, or sub-committee man for \{ILLEGIBLE\} Footb
all Club. He was very interested in it and he also knew one or two of the chaps that played, you know, very good players, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So this would interest you, of course, being a boy, you would like to hear all about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I was very keen on football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did he attend the races at all? Did he ever go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, if he had any money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But how often would he have gone do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I don't think he'd've gone very often in the year, I don't think ... he might go to see the Gr
and National, something like that, but I haven't known him to have gone, but I've known him to tell us, like, when he'd been to Chester, what it's like there, so he must have been to Chester races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And did he bet, do you know, if he went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, he had the working man's bet, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 A little flutter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Nothing, anyway, to break his home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father or mother belong to any savings clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Savings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, such as boot, or sick, or funeral clubs? Now you mentioned your mother used to belong to clothes clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, clothes, yes. Cheques.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Anything else that she belonged to? Any sick clubs, or what they called boot clubs, or funeral clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, she paid it through the cheque, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you get on with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, very well
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was there one there that you particularly felt close to? When you were in your school days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You felt the same way about them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I felt the same way about them all, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 As a child who did you play with, your brothers and sisters, or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, played with the neighbours, and brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 All together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. Good mixers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where did you play, in the yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If it was favourable we used to always try to get down to the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was a favourite place, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes, if it was favourable, like, the weather was ... in our ... such as light nights. We didn't believe in knocking round the neighbours and smashing windows, so we went took the ball to the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And if you couldn't get to the park would you play in other people's home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We might go in other people's homes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What games did you play mostly when you were little, when you played with your pals and your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Cricket, football and tying the cotton to the people's knockers and running away. (laughter) Anything for fun. What we used to love mostly, the best one we used to get was when the snow was on the ground, to make 
a snow castle. And the Corporation men in them days used to come down and see the sewers were all right, you know, and they used to have green candles. I don't know whether you've ever seen them. And these used to be in bunches like bananas, you know, abo
u
t 12. Well, we always managed to get one to 2 of those, and of course, that would be our lighting equipment inside the castle and we'd sit there, have some sort of games. Them somebody would blow the candles out and we'd have to hide ourselves. But mostly
 games as Relive-o and Find the Slipper or safety-pin, something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, that was Hobson's choice. We used to get dirty (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I mean what happened to you when you came home dirty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, we used to have to get stripped off and get washed right away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But you weren't told you weren't to get dirty, you mean? You just got dirty and you never thought about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we went home ... we had to get dirty because
 it came that way natural, you see. Even playing football you'd get dirty from head to foot, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased? Or did your parents day 'you are not to play with that child'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You were free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. The only time we were told was ... In my recollection the only time we were told was if, say, there was an i
nfection about, you see, such as measles or chicken pox, anything like that, well you'd be told, like, to stay away for a few days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was purely for fear of infection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's right, spreading infection.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you belong to any youth organisations? You mentioned the boys' club. What was it you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I belonged to the Social Club.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The boys' club before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Before I left school? Oh, no, only the Cadets, that's the only thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's the only thing that you belonged to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's all I was interested in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now I'd like to ask how you spent your free time when you were at school. Did you have any hobbies then? Did you keep any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 My hobby was I wanted to be a good singer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You really enjoyed singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Get to parties, you know, and sing to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you keep any pets at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
We only had the one rabbit, as I remember. We might have had a pup, like, as well, but they didn't belong to me, we had them in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you collect anything at all? You know how some children collect things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 As a youth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, yes, I used to collect a lot of silver paper, and that and send it to these ... I don't know whether it was Guide Dogs then or what it was, but it was for some cause.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you go fishing, or for walks, or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, we used to go for walks. And I've done bicycling, too. We used to side a bicycle at the shop we worked at, in the fish shop.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You didn't have a bicycle before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You only had one when you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever go fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Fishing, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who would you have gone for walks with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, some school mates, or me brothers and sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you take part in any sports? I know you mentioned that you used to go and play, but you played in a team?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I did play in a team, yes, but I wasn't a great footballer, you know. Me brother was a bit of a good footballers, the one that's dead now. He won the Expres
s Gold Medal, I think. But I was interested in the committee work of the team more than anything. I was the Sports Secretary, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So you obviously organised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, when I ask you did you go to any theatres, well, you mentioned that you went to variety things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you go to any concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Or any cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 While}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 At school? Oh, no. Went to concerts, but not cinemas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Just an ordinary, variety.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Variety concerts. Did your parents give you any pocket money whilst you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How much would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 About twopence a week, I think. That was me father's side of the j
ob, that. Saturday penny. And he might give us a penny on Sunday. No, when he took us to the theatre Saturday night, first thing we'd walk to West Derby Road from Lodge Lane, and of course, sweets were about 4 ozs. a penny, you know. We'd have a pennywort
h of sweets to go in, and then he'd pay for us to go in to the theatre, it'd be about 2 1/2d. or 3d., I think, but while I .... What was the question, again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We were talking about pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We used to keep our penny until we were coming home 
and then, down one of the streets we used to come they used to do the chips and the fish and all that crackle stuff that used to come off them. We used to go in and buy a penn'th of that and eat it all the way home. Very nice, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's what you mostly spent your penny on, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I used to spend my penny on that, and the other ... And if I didn't spend my penny, well one of the others'd spend theirs and then I'd keep mine and go and get sweets on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, I must say that we had very good neighbours and if there was anything wrong with Mother, you know, in all shapes and forms, like, we always had a very willing neighbour. And Mother used to do the same for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sort of things would they do for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, they'd, like, make a baked custard, you know, or come in and see if we were all right. You know, and they might help the eldest sister to get our food out for us. Oh, yes, very good neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how would she manage? I presume that these neighbours helped when she was ill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We did what we could do. We did our part.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember what happen
ed when one of your younger brothers or sisters were born? Can you remember the birth of any of your younger brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, not actually, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did she cope? Did she go into hospital to have her baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, she had it at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And how did everyone manage whilst she was having this baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the neighbours ... helping each other, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, more often than not, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How much of them did they see? Did they see a lot of their relatives, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think they did see a lot of their relatives, no.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If they did see them, where would they have seen them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, probably see them out shopping, or they may have had news that something wa
s wrong, or they wanted a discussion about something and then they'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And go round to their house, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents have friends? Not relatives. Can you remember any friends your parents may have had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I think me
 mother had a very old friend, a very grateful person. She used to help Mother, and one thing and another, and always enquiring about each other, you know what I mean. More like two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would they have gone to each other's houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Probably, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And she would have come to your home, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents share the same friends? Can you remember any friends that your parents had that were friends of both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I think so. I think they did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And 
you mentioned that your mother had this particular friend of her own? What about your father, did he have any particular friends of how own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I don't think he made any single friends, like, you know. The majority of his friends were chaps that w
orked at the docks, or public house friends, you know what I mean, like.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Can you remember friends being invited into the home? You mentioned this friend of your mother coming. Can you remember anybody else in the way of friends being invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Only some of our school mates, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But not your parents' friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I don't think they made a lot, you know, they were mostly ..... I could trip up on that question.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When anyone did come, particularly this friend of your mothers, would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. Oh, yes, a cup of tea, or ... that'd be one of the first things on the programme, that would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That never changes, does it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there particular days or occasions when you had people call? What about Christmases, and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, well, New Year, like, you know. We wouldn't have 'em in for parties, or anything like that, but they'd just call, just to ... They may have a drop of Port wine, if we had any, a
nd if it wasn't it'd probably be the female'd stop and have a chat with Mother and me father would go out with the chap and have a pint and back again, and then the might have a bit of supper before they go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you say that the friends you had for these occasions were your mother's friends or your father's friends, or both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Both I should think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not ... only to, say, make enquiries about the health of the family, someth
ing like that which ... that can lead up to anything. That can lead up to 'come inside and have a cup of tea', you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I suppose this would apply to neighbours, too, would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
What do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends or neighbours? Did they have musical evenings, or play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not with any exception, as I can recall it, no. I think the family woman comes in there, just the same
. I think she made her own bit of enjoyment at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And the home was enough for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Many people divide society into different social classes or groups. At that time, before 1918, did you think of some people belonging to one and some
 to another? And could you tell me what the different ones were, if you can think of people belonging to different social classes or groups.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did I think ...? Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Could you tell me what the different ones were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, different section
s, social groups, like, as far as I was concerned was those that tried to be high and mighty, you know, what I call the superior complex people and you knew that they were a bit above their standard by trying to be there. And then, of course, cliques was 
t
he other one. That's what I call the group, these cliques, even at your work, or anything like that. Even in a shop like Lewis's, you can guarantee amongst the staff there'll be cliques, never mind anything else. Oh, yes, I always thought that there was s
omebody trying to be ... in fact, we used to use a term 'twopence-ha'penny toffs'. You've heard that term, haven't you? And then we used to say 'all dressed up and no food in the house'. In other words trying to be something above their means.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What abo
ut the other people, not this type of person, but what other social classes would you have thought existed in that time, before 1918? How would you have described the social classes? What names would you have given them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the classes that were formed ... before 1918, did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Never mind, if you find that difficult, we'll go on to the next one. Which class, or group (but I think 'group' is the wrong word because it's not so much little cliques I want, it the class of person, you know, the
 class of society you think they belong to). Which class would you say you belonged to yourself up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Which class would I belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, what do you think you did up to 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It was a working people's class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sort of people
 belonged to the same sort of class as yourself, the working people's class? What other kind of people belonged to that class would you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I should think anybody that was ... well, anybody that was a manual labourer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sort of people 
belonged to the other classes or groups? Now, you haven't mentioned any, but I imagine that there must have been other classes or groups. What sort of people would you put into different classes, at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I should put ... in a class I'd l
ike to see people who are supervisory, you know what I mean. I mean people that really could put themselves in a supervisory job and hold the job and be fair with it. I mean to say, don't let the job get you down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What class of person would you say that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I would say a person that knew his business and knew the job and was a good mixer, that he could think of the days when he was just the ordinary labourer and then just think the same when he gets to supervisory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And feel for the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, never. Not to treat them differently, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you ever taught to touch your cap, show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes, definitely. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What were you told to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Anybody that you knew, more so the female, and the male, if you passed them in the street, 'good morning', always touch your cap, and always use good manners if it was the matrix, to the best of your ability, like, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was there anyone you called 'sir', or 'master', or 'madam' in particular, can you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I used to have a habit of saying, such as to whoever I was working for, the boss ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Before I left school, yes, in the fish business, I used to call even my boss - his name was Mr. Tom Tipping - I used to say 'good morning, sir', 'good afternoon, sir', 'good evening, sir'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was your way of showing respect to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 My way of showing respect, like. The way I was taught to show it, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the district where you lived who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, who were thought to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I don't know as I can say as anybody, because we all seemed to be pretty good neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about people who lived, not necessarily in th
e same street, but in who lived in Liverpool 8, in the district. Who were considered to be the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the most important people to me would be the people that was partly into our way of living, if you understand what I mean, tha
t could assist us to provide food and clothing, and all this sort. They were very important to the likes of us, you see, otherwise we wouldn't have clothes to put on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But who do you think considered themselves to be the most important people in the di
strict? Who do you think were the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
The most important people in any district in my neighbourhood were the people who were sociable and able to get on with ... People who were always willing to help each other. They are the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, you feel they were important because they were easy to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, always willing to assist.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, to refresh your memory, Mr. Mainey, do you remember we were talking about who you considered to be the most important people an
d we discussed that in the area that you lived in, do you remember? We were talking about what people you considered to be the most important and we got past that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What was my answer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, you said the people who were co-operative and helped you, you know, that you respected most of all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes, that's right. They are very important when you can go and just tell them, like, that your wife ... your mother's bad, or something like that and they come over and assist you, you know. In comparison,
 like, to these days. Nobody seems to worry these days, unless there's a will behind it, something like that (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about these people - I'm going to suggest a few people to you and I want you to try and think who they'd have been friendly wi
th, who they'd have been associated with? Firstly, who do you think shopkeepers would have associated with, who would have been their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, the people who spent the most money in their shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You would think so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, I would think so. You can't run a business unless you get the money out of them, can you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about the clergy, who would they have associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, they have all these little bits of organisations such as the youth club, and then the mothers' ..
. don't they have the mothers normally? Oh, I think the clergy was pretty well mixed all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
You don't think they had any particular kinds of friends? Can you think of any examples of the kind of friends the clergy might have had, what kind of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about teachers, who would they have associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I don't know. Have you any clues, like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, you know, who do you think they would have been friendly with, who they would have met and gone out with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Now what about farmers? I know there were some farmers living right in Liverpool at the beginning of the century, who would they have associated with, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Farmers generally associated with farmers, and farmers' wives, you know. In the country that is their association, but insofar }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 as well}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
, I should think the likes of Mr. Charles White in Queen's Square, they were the farmers' best friends when they sell their produce on commission and all this sort. But generally, all round, farmers mix with farmers. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about employers at that time, who do you think they would have associated with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Employers? Well, a good employer - what I mean is a sociable employer all round, I should think that he 
would associate just the same off duty with his workmen as he would on duty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You think he would be friendly with them in the evening, or do you think he'd have other friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, he'd have other friends as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of people do you think his friends would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Business people, I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sort of people would you say went to the Church that you attended when you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I'll tell you the sort of people, very mixed. Some are at the Church because they are b
elievers in their religion, but as I say, Ken Dodd and a few, they have a great train of \{ILLEGIBLE\}
 and all that sort and they used to criticise the people how they were dressed, because I know we've been criticized, my brother and I, he's dead now, we us
ed to get a suit on the cheque, you know, for Easter or Whit. But we know that we've been criticised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Why were you criticised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, because we had a new suit on and they're scratching their head, wondering whether it's been paid for cash down, 
or whether it's been on a cheque.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This is what people did, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, the same with females, you know. 'Oh, look at Lily Ashton, she's got a new dress on', you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sorts of people generally speaking, you say they were a mixed
 bunch, but what kinds of people do you think - apart from this type of person who figured out where the new suit came from - what other kinds of people attended the same Church as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, business men, and, you know, quite a lot of people holding different positions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
What about Chapel? Did you know much about Chapel? I know you said you were R.C., but what sort of people went to Chapel? Did you know anyone who went to Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Outstanding people, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 People that you know, you know, people that you came into contact with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, they were pretty good all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They were good Christians, well, mostly in the middle class, when we used to go, like, to 9 o'clock Mass on a Sunday or
 10 o'clock, and I think the big business people went to the 11 o'clock Mass.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This is in the R.C. Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When I say 'chapel' what does that mean to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It just means Church just the same, as far as I'm concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Can you remember any friction between Catholics and Protestants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Only the ... mostly with school children. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 
They used to have a great saying when walking along the street going to school before 9 o'clock or even just after dinner time on their way to school, and St. Patrick's day, or 12}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 th}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113  July, there used to be a great saying then, I.or O., that's Irish or Orange. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
That was the school children, and if I said I. and he said O., well I'd get a belt on the back of the head with something or other. Oh, yes, there used to be friction in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the worst I felt about religion was when I lived in Windsor Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was this when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I was a young man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. But when the ch
ildren ... I like to see children of all denominations on their days out, you know, who look well and hope they have nice weather and everything else, 'cos on this particular day there was people in houses throwing bags of pepper and it nearly come to a b
it of friction there, like, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Throwing pepper at whom? At the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
At the parade, like, the children from the Orange Lodge, like. And it was always on either of those two days, mostly on the parades of the Lodges with the police out 
in Hill Street, because the Church at the bottom was named St. Patrick's Church so, of course, that rang a bell, you see. And then the party tune used to be played and they used to play it up to the hilt there to try and draw us, you know. But that's the 
only religious set that I saw.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Where you lived, round about Cam Street, did all the people in the working class people group that you said you felt you belonged to, did they have the same standard of living, or would you say there were different groups
? Now, in that type of person that you felt you were and that other people who lived nearby, were there different standards of living, or did they have the same standards of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh no, there were different standards then, because I mean to say, t
he dole and the means test which you already mentioned, they ... some of them if they went to apply for assistance and that - I think I mentioned this to you last week - was when they had the inspectors coming round and if they had a piano, or something l
i
ke that they said 'well that to keep yourself', you see. Well, the likes of me, like, I started with the railway when I was very young, of course I completed me 48 years, so that was my life, like, I always had money to bring home every week, you see, but
 
there was many poor unfortunate labourers who perhaps had no pay for weeks on end. I think I told you about me father, what they called 'Three on the hook and 3 on the book', well, that was the hook, the docker's work weapon, you see, what he used to hand
le cargo with, and '3 on the book' was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 signing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Allowing for the fact that these people were sometimes short of money through not being able to work, apart from that people who were earning the same amount of money as yourself and your family, did t
hey have different standards, not because they were short of money, but because anyway they looked at life differently. Can you think of anyone who had different standards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I can't say I can think of any one, but there was always ... I don't care wh
at district anybody goes in you'll always find a locality where the people are practically the same category insofar as their living, but you'll always find the one or two that think that they're a bit higher than anybody else. I expect it happens everywh
e
re, not only in the neighbourhood. I mean to say, you always ... in a factory, or even the works, or anywhere at all where they're all on the same rate of pay, and trade unionism, and that, but you'll always find there's one or two, whether female or male
 that think they're a bit above the others. I think you'll find that's pretty general, that. It's, like, an impression. I give it to you that way, that they are somebody bigger than anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So you felt that some groups thought they were superior to the rest, but you didn't feel they had any right to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, I didn't feel that anybody didn't have any right to it, but it's just the sort of position they were putting on, like, you know. They didn't want to know you, sort of business, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were some families thought of as rough, and others as respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes. There were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of family would you have thought of as rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, if there was a family where the father and mother had the children in early in the
 evening, or they were told to come straight home from school, well then, boys will be boys and girls will be girls, but you'll always get groups now even young college boys, if you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 say 
\lquote be back at}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  four o'clock \{ILLEGIBLE\}}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
 They might be really good boys a
t home, and that, but they have these little games, and that, going on and they might get a bit roughish and then, of course, that's it. One mother might say, 'oh, those children are very rough, aren't they, they should be kept in hand', and all this sort
 of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about the parents themselves, though, did you think of some families as being respectable and others rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not ... the parents weren't what you call rough, like. They lived as neighbours, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your father and mother have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, yes. Well, Mother was always ... you know, liked to put the bright side on, same as we were taught, like. To always doff your hat to a lady, or give your seat on a bus or a tramcar to a lady, and 'good morning', or 'good evening', like that, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And your father, did he have the same attitude as your mother, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, they believed in everybody showing their manners and being very courteous with everybody. That's the only word I can use.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, I think the only thing on me mother's mind was that she was a mother and she had a family and that was it. That's what we looked on her as, a mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That was her life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. Oh, yes, we were definitely her life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You don't think she thought of herself as belonging to any particular class, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, n
ot exactly possible because the class, if you're referring to the different organisations in that respect, well, those that hadn't got the money, they couldn't mix with those that had got it, you see, because they had none. What was the question again?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
You just stayed in your ... if you hadn't got the finance to move round, like, you were just ... you just clique up together and with your neighbour, and go to the park, which I think I said before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember anyone being described as a 'real gentleman' or a 'real lady'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the same class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, what do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I think we have ... I have, meself, classified people as a real lady or a real gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Why would you have done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, because they were always so very nice to me and everybody else in my estimation, like, what I'd seen of them. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You wouldn't have called them 'a real gentleman' or a 'real lady' for any other reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, well, it's the little deeds, say, they did for the poor people. Might be a person come round and do this or do that or the other for the poor, and all this sort, you know. I wouldn't say they were real ladies, but they were very thoughtful lad
ies and very helpful ladies, and gentlemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would you call a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, I would call a real lady ... say, a young girl that I went to school with and she grew up and she never altered her ways, always courteous, kind to everybody and 
one thing and another, and up to the time she died she still carried out her good deeds, and that for anybody else. I should criticise her a real good lady. By the word 'good' I mean ... I don't mean, like, high and mighty, or anything like that. She was 
really good to everybody and you could say she was a real lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would you call somebody who you thought was high and mighty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, somebody as tries to be king of the castle and all this sort of business, you know, and a boaster. Never liked
 people who boasted a lot, such as a woman saying, 'oh, my children are far superior to anybody else's', and according to God, coming back to the Bible, well, we're all God's children, you see, so far as that goes and why anybody should think that their c
hildren were ... either the father or the mother, should think that their children were high above anybody else and gave that impression that the other crowd were just ... we'll say, litter in the street sort of business.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember this happening when you were a child? Do you remember anybody saying this or thinking this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What, that they were higher than us?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, as a family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, I don't say that they said it directly, but they'd give you the opinion, like, when you've ... we
ll, their actions, like, they'd give you the opinion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I used to think that they were all good men, policemen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you were naughty, did your mother ever say 'I'll call a policeman'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I used to take it to heart, specially when you broke a lamp or something she'd say 'next time you do that I'll bring a policeman to you'.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But you thought they were all good fellows?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you like to say anything more about them, what else did you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, talking about it, in my younger days we lived in a rough quarter, like, you know. I'll quote you one i
nstance, if I'm not going to use your tape too quick. There used to be a stable at the top of the street and there used to be 4 men lived and slept in that stable, you see. And I learnt in later years that they were 4 pretty well educated men of good fami
l
ies but they were outcasts insofar as the family was concerned and they were left to ... so much money a month they used to get and they used to have some real tough nights of a Saturday night with the police, and that, and there used to be one fellow use
d
 to take 7 policemen to put him in the Black Maria. And, of course, you get these 4 men, like, and they'd had a lot of beer down them or hooch, or whatever you like to call it and any row broke out, well one constable he'd have to face the 4, and they wer
e 4 real good ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And how did the policeman cope with this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, he had to ... Well, there used to be one policeman ... my opinion was that sooner than look a man up he'd sooner give them a good doing over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And let it go at that, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, I suppose, like, he thought he'd be taking too much on, like, by himself. But the police, well, we always looked upon the police as guardians and good men.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And how do you think they treated people generally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Very good. Very good, especially people who were infirm, or short-sighted or anything like that. Very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They always showed a kindly hand to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Was your home rented in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you see anything of your landlord, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, he used to come for the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you feel about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think he was just an ordinary working man. That's how I thought of him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did your parents think about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, me mother always spoke well of t
he owners of the house, whether you're going to class him as a landlord, or ... Well, his name was Smith and he was very well like, so far as me mother and that was concerned. If she wanted anything doing, or when we moved which I mentioned, on two or 3 o
ccasions, it seemed to be into his houses. So I must say that he was very good as far as that was concerned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, they did at times, until we all got to school-leavi
ng age, like. I told you I left school at 13, you see, and it was on application from me parents to see if they get me off school and I went to a fish shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I've got lots to talk about that in a minute. What did you think about it being difficult for your parents to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, I used to be very sympathetic with them, you know, because I knew very well that the work wasn't there for me father, he could only do it when it was there and he did his best to get what he could and I don't I d
on't think he ever left us without a meal, like, although he liked his beer which I told you, like. But I think me mother and father ... we used to be a bit down in the dumps when we couldn't do something to bring us up to a decent standard. When we got w
orking, of course, we made up for it then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What difference did it make to the family when your father was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It didn't make any difference to us, like, but ... insofar as when he was out of work, like, because as I say, there was work to do.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But what difference did it make to the family, what did you notice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We didn't notice any difference in our life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, we still got a meal, even if it was only hash or something made up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Your mother was ingenious, was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It was always there; soups, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever get help from The Guardians, or any parish, or the charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I don't think so, I wouldn't like to 'yes' or no' because I never went so far as to ask me father or mother, or get to know of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Now I'm going to start talking about school. Were you given lessons by one of your parents, a tutor or a governess? Before you went to school you didn't get taught at home, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I should say five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you first started what time of the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 We went at 9 o'clock, school starting time, until 4 o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you come home for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you started school at five, did you start half a day, or the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Went the whole day. Used to break from 12 o'clock 'till 1.30. Nine 'till 12, and 1.30 'til 4.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of school was it? Was it a Church school or an ordinary Council school, or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, it was known as St. Bernard's R.C. School, 'cos the Church as St. Bernard's, you see, but the Liverpool Education Committee had connections with it because, as I told you when ... the last year or so, when I was goin
g to the St. Thomas Street, just taking registers and that, or any notes that had to go down, that was the Liverpool Education offices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you get to school and how long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Walk. Two minutes, 3 minutes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It was quite close?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. The furthest one was about 6 or 7 minutes, that was from Handel Street to ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This isn't the first school, though, that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Which?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The one we're talking about now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The first one I went to Was Lady Mount }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 Carnell up}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  Park Street, but I don't remember going there very long before we moved up to Handel Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I see, this was your first school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It was me longest school, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The one you were at the longest, you mean, or the furthest away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, the longest I was at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who went with you? Did you go on your own or did somebody take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, the eldest ... well, we had both ways, sometimes they'd go with me and sometimes I'd go on me own. That was me eldest brother and sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They used to keep an eye on you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you think there is any point in my talking to you about Mount Car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 mel}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  School, because were you very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I wouldn't remember a lot. I only remember where the school was and where the Church was. I wasn't old enough, or clever enough, then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now you had your midday meal at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you think of the school itself? This is St. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 Bernard\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I liked it, meself. I like it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, diff
erent opinions, different teachers. You see, some teachers were very good, you see, they'd set you to do something and they'd leave you to do it and others, see, and other teachers would perhaps get ... not with me, personally, like, but others might get 
a bit irritable and think you're taking too long over a sum, or something like that, and I think that used to put some of us off our balance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, if you're trying to reckon something up and somebody comes in between you while your mi
nd's going. I should put it down the same as if 2 females are talking and a bit of business and blethering at you, which sums you refer to business, the same as anybody else and in between calls you ... first of all you turn round and say, like I turn rou
nd and say to you' what was the question, where were we up to?' You simply let it slide out of your mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You lose your train of thought, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you felt the teachers hurried you too much, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the majority were very good. Of course, the cane was being used them days and I don't think it's used so much these days, and that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would you have got the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, you'd have got the cane for doing something you shouldn't do, or back-chatting the teach
ers or as I say, they might say you're not interested in your lessons, something like that. But you'd only get a smack on the hand.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 With the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 With the cane, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did it hurt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. Oh, they made sure they gave you a little tingle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there girls and boys at the school, or just boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Girls and boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about the girls, were they punished in the same way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, they all got the cane, yes, if they were caught out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners, or tidiness or punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, the teachers were there to teach you how to speak. Oh, they weren't bad on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, they did with me, and the brothers and the sisters. They were with all. Me father was pretty clever and, of course, we'd depend on him for anything difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 He would help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, 'what was your subject to-day', or 'how did you think you went on' and all this sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they visit the school or meet the teachers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think the only time they visited the school, I think, w
as when there was any doctors or dentists. They used to examine their teeth, and that. I think they used to ask for the mothers to be present. The fathers, I don't think they had to call on them for much, unless they wanted bring you down to tell you to c
hastise your family, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And that was really the only time they would meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I think that was, yes. In general I found them pretty good all round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the other children at St. Bernard's School come from similar types of homes to your own, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, different to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What kind of different types?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
People that were better off than us and also the ... always had a bit of coloured, in my days at the school, so we can't say what their parents' line of business was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Coloured children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, Chinese and ... yes. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
What kinds of homes, then, would you have thought the people who thought they were superior to you would have come from? What kind of work would their parents have done, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I should think they would have been, like, some sort of importers or something like that, you know, like, in a mild form. Of course, in a big form they'd have probably gone to a collegiate or something higher up, but I should thi
nk they'd be ... well, I don't know what to put them down as. Produce growers or something like that. These foreigners, you know, they went ... we couldn't tell what their ... of course, Chinese laundries, and that, some of their fathers had those. We did
n't have Chinese chip shops then, not like they have now. But there used to be mixed nationality at the school, so to give a really good 100% answer on that, I don't think I could manage that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Insofar as education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, in the way they treated them, educationally or in other ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think so. They may have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 had one}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  or two that they thought differently about but I don't think they showed it to any extent. There was always the favourite, like, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, I mean to say, take me, like, for the two years, you see, all I had to do was pick radishes and all this sort, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you were one of the favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Anybody seeing that'd say 'oh, he's the favourite', but they didn't realise that insofar as I know - and I'm not far out \{BLANK\}
 I practically learnt what I was expected to learn in the year, you see, and it'd 've been a waste of time me sitting down to go through the same sums as I'd already done because it'd be like reading a book about 10 times over.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes. The gangs. You don't get vicious gangs, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 If there were any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I don
't think so, not to do any depredation or to damage anybody, you know, like that. We had our little scraps and fights, like, you know. We'd have a fight, perhaps, about some fellow not having his hat on right, but no, I don't think they were wicked to the
 word wicked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
It would be at the parents' request, I should think, if they were, because ... well, I'm speaking mostly for meself, I like to get forward and see what's coming next, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about some of the other children, though, do you ever remember any child being left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, a few of them were a bit backward, like, and that, but whether they were pushed to one side, I don't know. But we in our family, we were
 always that way that we tried to make friends with everybody. And if we didn't, well, it'd be a job to tell what ... I don't think we were ever disliked, anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You didn't go on to another school from St. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 Bernard\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 ? It was just the Mount Car}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 mel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  Scho
ol which you went to for a very short time, and then St. Bernard's and that was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you were 13 when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 13, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I'd have stayed longer if I ...
 Well, what I'd have liked to have done if it could have been done was to go for the examination for the ... oh, what do you call it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Scholarship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Scholarship, yes. But I told you the reason of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The reason I didn't
 go for a scholarship was because me father couldn't afford to pay for the books, you see, and then we come to uniform, and that, well ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Wouldn't you have got any help from that, or wouldn't there have been assistance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I can't recollect that far back. I don't think you had the assistance towards further education in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's a fairly recent thing, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That was my ambition, was to go for a scholarship and win it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You would have liked to have done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, 
very much. I'd have sooner liked to have done that than the going backwards and forwards to St. Thomas with the registers, because there was nothing to that, but there'd be something interesting. And I might have been one of these high and }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 mighty's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  with a big job, you see. Never can tell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But there's no looking back on that, you made a success of your life, didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I made a success of my life as far as I've gone, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you attend any part time education afterwards, did you go to any evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Went to night school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me about that, how often would you have gone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, might be once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 For how long for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, one night, perhaps, a couple of hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Over what period of time would you have gone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 The usual school periods, barring summer holidays and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would it have been a year or would it have been 2 years or something like that, after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, after I left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. Did you go to any night classes after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, no, I don't think I did, not to me knowledge, no. I think I was more interested in the Cadets then, which I was talking about. That was my night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now when I ask you do you have any regrets about your education, at this stage, what would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 
The only regret I've got is the one I still insist on, it's if we'd've had the money I'd've gone for further education. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I'd've plumped for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You definitely relate this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I can talk the Queen's English now, and I'm a moderate writer and I'm pretty good at sums, and that. History, I don't think I was too good at history, I was very poorly moderate. No, I took it all in, you know, the best I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Whilst you were still at school - this is up to 13 - did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you get this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I used to go from 5 o'clock at night 'till ab
out 8 o'clock at night for half a crown a week, or 2 shillings a week. What they call a night and Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 At the fishmongers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you get it through your parents, this job, or did you get it through someone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Through meself.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 They wanted a boy, a night and Saturday boy, and I went and that was it. Me brother was in the same firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you just worked on the Saturday mornings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, evenings, and Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 All Saturday, or just Saturday morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 All Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How many hours would you have worked each evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Say about 3 hours of an evening, 5 'till 8, we'll say, and Saturday from ... oh, be about 12 hours on a Saturday. Cheap labour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you have to do in this job, did you serve in the shop or did you deliver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I delivered first of all until I learnt to fillet, score, bone and roll and all this sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And then you used to serve in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they give you any holidays at all with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, I don't think they did, not on nights and Saturday, no. The holiday they gave us, I told you, they sent us away, me and me brother, it was smashing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What were you paid for this part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Two shillings to half a crown.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you feel that was a fair wage, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, at that time I thought it was reasonable, in comparison. I mean to say, you'd work a full time job for say, 10, 11, to 12 hours a day and 12 hours Saturday, and you got half day off on a Wednesday, for about 6 bob or 7/6d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So that was pretty fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, in those days, yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you give any of the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Give it all to me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did your mother spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 To clothe us, and feed us. Whatever ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Whatever you needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Whatever was her heartaches ... what she needed the money for, that was how it was used.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 She would put it in with the rest and just ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, that's it. It all went in the kitty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you get on with the other people you worked with when you were working in this fish shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, good. Really good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did your employer treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Quite pleased, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, quite pleased.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I thought he was a good boss.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I enjoyed it, really enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did the job alter your attitude to school at all? Whilst you were still at school and you had this part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think so because the job was after school, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you do any other part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, only that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, I'd like to ask about your first full time job. What was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 My first full time was as a shop assistant in a fish shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In this same fish shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, he had 3 shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I see, so you went to another shop, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. If there was anybody going off sick or anything like that, you'd be sent to ... one of the other shops.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I see. So really you didn't change your place of employment at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You just sort of started to go full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you had to do exactly the same? Had you got past the delivering stage then, or were you always employed in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, serving the customers, cleaning the fish, etc. And then I went in for learning how to dress poultry and ....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What hours did you work when you started to work full time? You worked every day. Did you have a half day at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, we had Wednesday, Wednesday half day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 All day Saturday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And Sundays ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, we had Sunday off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I can only recollect that one holiday, as I told you. I don't think there was any holidays then, at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What were you paid when you worked there full time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 As I told you 6 bob to 7/6d.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you feel that was a fair wage for a full time job then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 At the time, like, in comparison to what ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This is what I mean, in comparison to other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you give any of the money that you earned to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 All of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did she ever give you anything back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When would she give you something back, for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, she'd give us something back on a Saturday, you see, and say 'well, there's your weekend money'. Might give you 6d. or a shilling, I just forget.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You could probably have a good time on that, could you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 When you left school and started to work full time, did your attitude to school change then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I'd lost the atmosphere of the school, like, but me attitude to
 the school didn't change because I was ... believed in my school, you know, I liked it while I was there. But my attitude didn't change, it was just that you weren't amongst the boys and girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How long were you there and what was your next job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Oh, I stayed in the fish until the War broke out and then I volunteered for the Army and I was told to go back and sleep in the bread bin for a bit longer (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How old were you when you first tried to volunteer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Between 16 and 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you went back to the fish shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. No, no, no, I got the sack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 From the fish shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, when I went back after trying to join the Army, when I went back I found there was somebody else in me job, so I finished up getting a job with the railway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That was when? How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 February 1915. Seventeen years of age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me about the railway, how did you get the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Walking along the dock road and asking was I out of work and being asked by a supervisor of
 the railway did I want a job, and I said 'certainly, that's why I walking round, looking for one'. I started at Duke's Dock, Liverpool, the Great Western Railway. I served with them for 48 years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What exactly did you have to do in this job when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I was a porter, handling goods, you know, general goods of all descriptions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not a passenger porter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, goods.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Goods porter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What hours did you work when you first started when you were 17?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Total hours a week, about 60 hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have a half day in that week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, you had what they call ... you had a shift there what they called 'early lates', that's a funny term, isn't it, 'early lates'? There was 'early early' and 'early lates'. If y
ou were on the early early you'd start at 7 o'clock and if you got off a 4 o'clock on a Saturday, well you were the lucky one ... your lucky day, and the others'd probably have to work 'till 6. Just on a flat rate of pay, no overtime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So this was 60 hours a week, every week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes, 60 hours a week. Seven 'till 6, six days a week, one hour for a meal. It worked on a 10 hours a day, see, but this Saturday, like, I think it was something that was made up amongst the men themselves, this early early an
d early late, you know. That was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes. After 12 months I think I got 2 days' holiday, and then I don't think I completed the second year when I would've got 3 days off only I was ... enlisted then, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What were you paid? When you went first to the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Twenty-one shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So that was quite a bit more than what you'd been getting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Do you feel that was a fair wage for what you were doing, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 A fair wage, yes. Well, it compared with a lot of jobs, like, on a flat rate of pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It compared well, or not well, with other jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It compared pretty well, within a few shillings, like. A policeman was only getting 29 shillings a week, then
; we were talking about policemen, weren't we? About 29 bob, I think, a bobby got
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you give any of this money, that you earned on the railways, to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you give all of it, or some of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I gave her, say ... give her about ... give her a pound of it and not the 2 bob, I think, or 3 bob, whatever it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What did you spend that on? That 3 bob that you kept.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, go to the pictures, or a football match, if it was just a local match, like, say wher
e you paid 3d. or 4d. You had your sweet money, your pot money or whatever it is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you get on with the other people you worked with on the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, very mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, being strange to the job, you see, fi
rst of all and of course, there's always somebody tries to be a bit bigger than the other and that was why I said to meself I'm going to advance meself as far as I can with this lot because there was such a lot of enmities. There was different ways of sli
n
ging stuff, there was different ways of handling stuff, you know, such as fragile stuff, and all this. Well, you were a new recruit and you might handle a case one road and then somebody else comes along and starts showing, like, his authority. He was no 
bigger in the job, like, than what you were. Oh, very mixed crowd. There were practically in all these union jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How would your employer treat you? Now this would be a person in this particular case because you can't have a direct employer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 He treated me as a good railway man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you feel about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I felt that he was all right. Well, we had different bosses, like, you know, they changed very often, but I think I suited the majority. They could see I was a willing horse and I was going to go places.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I was interested in the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did this job alter your attitude to school in any way or had you already got over that and anything you felt about ... '
cos you'd already been in a full time job before, hadn't you, so really that question isn't necessary. You worked with the railway until 19-- ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 '63.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. You remember you went into the Army, what year would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I went in the Army yes, in 1916.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You were invalided out of the Army, weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 That's right, in 1919.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So it was after that that you started again with the railways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, the job was kept open, you see, and you were given that time, you were 
credited with the time in the Forces on your return, like. Safe and good, like, you had to pass the doctor when you came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Now, you've been with the railways ever since you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 came out}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  of the War up to the time you retired in 1963?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 1963}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 , yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Tell me about the different posts that you got. I know what you ended up as, but for recording's sake ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I started as a goods porter, and then I got a bit interested in transport and I went as .. you call it a second man on a motor. That's like 
a driver's mate, you see, and learnt the ins and outs of what I wanted to learn so far as the loading of the vehicle, the discharging of the vehicle, the handling of the vehicle and then eventually went for a test and passed as a driver.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This is a train driver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
No, motor driver. And from there I went to the driver, and from the driver, as time went on I put in for promotion and got it, to a Senior Checker. I was a working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 foreman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 . There were, like, groups and grades, you see. Categories, like, bu
t these two, a carter - was the man handled the horse wagon, motor driver. Oh, no, a carter was classified as a checker, no. A motor driver and second man, and there was one or two other grades in the group where your line of promotion from motor driver w
ould be to working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 foreman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  or senior checker, you see. Well, you call it working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 foreman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 . And then, from working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 foreman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  to foreman, and then from foreman to inspector.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you got up to inspector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What year was that, when you were first made inspector?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Made inspector?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, 5 years before I retired. Say 1959, 1960, when I was made inspector.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you have preferred another type of profession? Or occupation? If you had your time over again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It's not so much a matter of time over again, it's a matter of finance. I would have liked to have been a lawyer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You would?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Something like that, you know, but of course, as I say, that the finance wasn't there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you serve an apprenticeship or trainin
g period for any of your jobs? Now obviously, when you first started in the fish shop, for instance you were trained, and then you were delivering until you sort the fish out and learn how to fillet and this sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 There was no training, no actual training, like. Well, you had to pick it up as you went along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But when you first joined the railway, this was an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 It was the lowest grade of the senior ... you know, once you turned 18 or 19, well, you could come on to what
 they call the men's staff, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And would you consider that your time in the railway was an apprenticeship and building up to what you eventually became?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well now, I made it me business, as I told you, like to go as far as I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you belong to any trade union organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And what would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 National Union of Railwaymen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you take part in any of its activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not officially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would you have done unofficially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, 
I was a good member, like, insofar as the Union was concerned. Well, good and bad. But as far as the Union was concerned, like, I'd great belief in it because it was necessary at those times because I'd seen the stigma, or felt the stigma of the 1911 stri
k
e with Bloody Sunday, which I mentioned before, which is the actual term, like, it's not a vulgar word, of the dock labourers and railwaymen, the General Strike, fighting for an existence and they had to have some kindness from somewhere. And of course, t
h
at was the days of Tom Mann, if you've ever heard of him, and he was the great leader of these people and of course, I thought to meself then, although I was only young, only 13 years of age then, I thought to meself then, well they should have some organ
i
sation of something or other, somebody to fight for them, but I didn't think it'd come as bad as it has at the present time where the trade union and the shops stewards are the firm now, practically. But in those times I thought it was necessary to have s
ome leadership.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What sort of things did you do unofficially, to take part in the activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
I used to go, say, to Union meetings and all this sort. I used to attend the Union meetings, I picketed when strikes were on, and all this sort, like, work it from branch to branch. Nothing in an official capacity, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You just helped out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Just helped out, like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests, or different ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, it was always different in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In what way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, the employer knew that he was the employer, you see, and you were his humble servant, if that the word I can use. Humble servant. And to the majority of employers, as far as I know, you had to just knuckle under to them. 
That's all. You had to look at them as to a god. They were your master, and that was it. If they employed you it was 'thank you very much, sir', and if they didn't employ you, well, you just had to turn about and make your way home. And of course, there w
as blue eyes in those days just the same as there is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 There were favourites, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Some favourites, you know, recommendations 'my father was this ...'; of course, there was recommendations everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Towards the work, or towards the union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Towards their attitudes, towards everything. Just generally speaking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think that there was any ... that they had anything against the work, because in th
ose days it was a matter that if you didn't do your job, out you went and you'd perhaps be a long time before you got a job, if any at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about their attitudes towards the Union, would there be much division of interests there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, 
there was a lot of non-unions, you see, because somebody's got to stay out and somebody's got to go ahead, you see, and of course, the same thing as I ... when you asked me about the members of Parliament, you see, that they have ideas of their own, you s
ee. Some didn't like the rules and regulations and some did and that it. But it was a long time before they got any sort of percentage in practically any union, I think. Now it's gone into millions, hasn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers. Did you feel that, or not?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Ah, yes. Well, I didn't feel it in the railway, but in many jobs I've seen it, where the man who was a craftsman, he thought he was the ... Statue of Liberty,
 like, and the other fellow was just a ... well 'my labourer' and that's all there is to it, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was how you felt about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, a lot did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you say that fulltime work changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, it didn't exactly change me life, but there was many a time when, I tell you, I was a bit ambitious as a ... a bit of a singer, like. Good singer in me younger days. I couldn't sing now, but I'd like to have had enough time to go in for a bit of sta
ge work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You would have liked to have done that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I would, yes. Especially in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 the minstrel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  line, the line of the old pierrots that's what I would have liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Really, that appealed to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes. Or the Black and White Minstrels, anything in that line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What were you, a tenor or a baritone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I was like, a comedian. I used to do Fred }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 Barney\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  stuff, 'Give me the moonlight, give me the girl ...' Frankie Vaugh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13258625\charrsid10310113 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
n sings that now, doesn't he. And 'Paddling }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10512896\charrsid10310113 Madeleine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113  Home' and ' \{ILLEGIBLE\} 'and all that sort.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Now, I want to talk to you about life after leaving school. I'd like to ask you about your life at home after you left school. Did you continue to live at home then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I lived at home until I got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2325890 Married}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no. No, no, it never would do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about your brothers and sisters, did it change your relationship ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, just one happy family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you spend your Sunday any differently? Did you still go to Church or Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Went to Church for a period of time and ... well, I don't know as I should say this, or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Please do, feel free to say what you want to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I lost a bit of faith when I saw the humans, and that, being killed around me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You mean during the War, was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Yes. Well, I didn't see them all, like, but they were ... what we knew and I happened to say 'well, why should this happen?' and of course, I brought the Lord into it and me 
own ... it's only me own feelings, like. And I thought to meself, well, if there is such a man as the Lord why doesn't he stop this right away. He's got the power, He's got the means to do it. Good men, you know. Well, there was Germans getting killed and
 
ours getting killed. He didn't know which of us ... what they wanted to kill me for, what I had to kill them for. It was just a feeling that ... I couldn't see that there was any sense in ... We knew we were canon fodder, we knew that. Once you enlisted, 
like, you were known as canon fodder, but then you come to see a lot of good people that you had living round you, and that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you think this had an effect on your faith, did you, and going to Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I just thought to meself, as I say, 
that ... it didn't have a great effect on me going to Church, you see, but you get all this ... the powers as I say, 'do this, do that, do the other' and I thought to meself, well, I wonder if it's real or imaginative, you see. And then these all good-liv
ing people - well, not all, but some living as well as they could, they're just people, they're just getting bowled over, and that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How long would you say you continued to go to Church, then, after you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, I went several times a year, like, but not regular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Did you take an interest in politics at this time? Now, you've already mentioned to me that you were a Union man and you took an unofficial interest in that. But tell me about politics. Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not an active interest. Oh, no. Never would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any views at all at that time in your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I was always Labour minded, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Why did you think that? Why were you Labour minded at that particular time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 
Well, because I had to work, just like an ordinary worker, and that and I said to meself, I'm one of the labourers, I'm not one of the high and mighty, like, and that was just it. I studied the rules, regulations, and that. Me father was Liberal, which I 
told you, and he believed in their ideas of free trade and tariff reform, in fact he used to harp that quite a lot. That was in Lloyd George's days, and that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you vote in a general election before 1919? How old would you have been then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And did you vote in that year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 General election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you would have voted Labour on that occasion, 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever feel under any pressure from anybody to vote for a particular party, or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I always used me own brain.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you didn't feel under any pressure at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were you a member of a political party? You said before you weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever work for one of the parties at an election unofficially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not a general election, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What about the local elections? Would you have done any work unofficially at that time for the Labour Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, I don't think I did. Perhaps give a few billheads out, something like that. No, I didn't do anything at all in the attic, like.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So you didn't take part in any political activity other than at election time when you voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No. And Council, like, you know. You had to vote in your own Council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 For the Union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, no, the local elections.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You told me earlier something of how you spent your spare time before you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the Cadets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 In the Cadets and you liked the park football ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Yes, round to the park and play football or cricket.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way when you left school and were working, or did you do different things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, well, you couldn't spend your time the same way because getting from school at 4 o'clock, we'd go to the park s
traight from school. Well then, you'd be working.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 You'd be working later, of course. So what did you do, then, did you go out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Used to go to the pictures, and that, the Granby or Princes, Myrtle Street, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Who would go with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Some of the mates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So your boy friends; any girl friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Not when we was going to school, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 After you left school this was, don't forget. When you were working. But then you were still quite young when you started to work.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 I'd no interest in girls until after the First World War. That's when I met the wife, about 1919, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So you didn't make any girl friends at all up to the time of the War, up to the time you came back from the War, really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you make any new friends, boy friends, at work when you first started to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, with me workmates, oh, yes. Of course, we had a football team, and one thing and another, a social ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 This was with the railway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes. Railway Social Club, such as the one in Dean Road which holds about 3,000, I believe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Would you have met these friends at work, these new friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Some of them at work, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Where would you have met the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Only the neighbours, round about, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, I dare say, yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 No, never made any special friends. Not to stand out, they were all mates and pals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 And you would go out to the pictures. Anything else you would do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Go to a football match, or a polo match at the swimming baths, and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, they met one or two, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they expect to know where you were, your parents, when you were out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, we used to pretty well tell them where we was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Did they expect you to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 What would they say to you, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Well, 'be in by 9 o'clock', or
 if we were going to the water polo at Lodge Lane baths which didn't finish 'till half past nine, 'be in by a quarter to ten'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How old would be when they told you this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Round about the 13 or 14 mark, I should say
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 How old did you have to be before your parents wanted to know where you were going, and when they told you what time to come home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, could be any age from 9 years to 14.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 But after you reached 14 were you more or less able to go where you wanted to without telling them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 So long as you had somebody with you, like, but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14361825 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Were they still particular about the time you came in, or not?
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\s15\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid14361825 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2166563 SM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16468100\charrsid10310113 Oh, yes, you had the time laid down. If you were going to the second house at the pictures you must be in by half past 10, 
to 11, like. But that was only, say, once a week. It wasn't a regular thing, like. Oh, no, they'd start to worry if it got after a certain time
\par }}